<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="319" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1447,2014]" pageId="13" pageNumber="319">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1447,1473]" pageId="13" pageNumber="319">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
In the keys of 
<bibRefCitation author="Lundbeck, W." box="[435,627,1447,1473]" pageId="13" pageNumber="319" refId="ref14900" refString="Lundbeck, W. (1922) Diptera Danica Part VI Pipunculidae, Phoridae. Wesley, London, 447 pp." type="book" year="1922">Lundbeck (1922)</bibRefCitation>
it runs to Group VI couplet 32 lead 
<specimenCount box="[1023,1074,1447,1473]" pageId="13" pageNumber="319" type="generic">
2 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schmitz)" baseAuthorityName="Schmitz" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[1043,1074,1448,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impolluta">
<emphasis box="[1043,1074,1448,1473]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="319">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</specimenCount>
impolluta (Schmitz), a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wood)" baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[180,409,1483,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sylvatica">
<emphasis box="[180,316,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="319">M. sylvatica</emphasis>
(Wood)
</taxonomicName>
, but its hypopygium is clearly different. In the key to the males of the British species (
<bibRefCitation author="Disney R. H. L." pageId="13" pageNumber="319" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref14009" refString="Disney R. H. L. (1989) Scuttle Flies-Diptera Phoridae Genus Megaselia. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 10 (8), Royal Entomologicai Society of London, 1 - 155. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631287 X 00115" type="book chapter" year="1989">Disney, 1989</bibRefCitation>
) it runs to couplet 232, but its hypopgium fits neither option. In Borgmeier’s (1966) key to Nearctic Group VII it runs to couplet 21 lead 
<specimenCount box="[436,488,1555,1581]" pageId="13" pageNumber="319" type="generic">
2 
<taxonomicName authority="Borgmeier" authorityName="Borgmeier" authorityYear="1966" box="[457,488,1556,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="postcrinata">
<emphasis box="[457,488,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="319">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</specimenCount>
postcrinata Borgmeier, but its costal index is only about 0.44.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="319" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1447,2014]" pageId="13" pageNumber="319">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1591,1617]" pageId="13" pageNumber="319">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Frons as 
<figureCitation box="[522,603,1591,1617]" captionStart="FIGURES 97–107" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[296,1292,181,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-19@14.[290,1297,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 97–107. Megaselia hojerensis n. sp., 97, frons; 98, postpedicels, palps and prpboscis; 99, side of thorax; 100, left side of thorax and abdomen; 101, left view of hypopygium; 102, left hypandrium; 103, right view of hypopygium; 104, front tarsus; 105, segments 3–5 of front tarsus; 106, hind femur; 107, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925239/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="319">Fig. 97</figureCitation>
, with dense but very fine microtrichia. Cheek with 3 bristles and jowl with 2 that are longer and more robust. Postpedicels, without SPS vesicles, palps and proboscis as 
<figureCitation box="[1222,1305,1627,1653]" captionStart="FIGURES 97–107" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[296,1292,181,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-19@14.[290,1297,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 97–107. Megaselia hojerensis n. sp., 97, frons; 98, postpedicels, palps and prpboscis; 99, side of thorax; 100, left side of thorax and abdomen; 101, left view of hypopygium; 102, left hypandrium; 103, right view of hypopygium; 104, front tarsus; 105, segments 3–5 of front tarsus; 106, hind femur; 107, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925239/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="319">Fig. 98</figureCitation>
, the labella lacking short spinules below. Thorax with 3 notopleural bristles and no cleft in front of these, and mesopleuron bare (
<figureCitation box="[160,245,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURES 97–107" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[296,1292,181,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-19@14.[290,1297,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 97–107. Megaselia hojerensis n. sp., 97, frons; 98, postpedicels, palps and prpboscis; 99, side of thorax; 100, left side of thorax and abdomen; 101, left view of hypopygium; 102, left hypandrium; 103, right view of hypopygium; 104, front tarsus; 105, segments 3–5 of front tarsus; 106, hind femur; 107, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925239/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="319">Fig. 99</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with an anterior pair of small hairs and a posterior pair of bristles. Abdomen as 
<figureCitation box="[1293,1389,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURES 97–107" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[296,1292,181,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-19@14.[290,1297,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 97–107. Megaselia hojerensis n. sp., 97, frons; 98, postpedicels, palps and prpboscis; 99, side of thorax; 100, left side of thorax and abdomen; 101, left view of hypopygium; 102, left hypandrium; 103, right view of hypopygium; 104, front tarsus; 105, segments 3–5 of front tarsus; 106, hind femur; 107, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925239/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="319">Fig. 100</figureCitation>
, the gray venter with small hairs on segments 3–6. Hypopygium as 
<figureCitation box="[861,1017,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURES 97–107" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[296,1292,181,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-19@14.[290,1297,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 97–107. Megaselia hojerensis n. sp., 97, frons; 98, postpedicels, palps and prpboscis; 99, side of thorax; 100, left side of thorax and abdomen; 101, left view of hypopygium; 102, left hypandrium; 103, right view of hypopygium; 104, front tarsus; 105, segments 3–5 of front tarsus; 106, hind femur; 107, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925239/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="319">Figs 101–103</figureCitation>
, the hypandrium with a pale left lobe but no right lobe, and the epandrium has a bristle each side that is longer than the subequal hairs on the rest and those of the cerci, proctiger and at the rear of tergite 6. Legs yellow. Fore tarsus with posterodorsal hair palisade on segments 1–5 (
<figureCitation box="[320,520,1843,1870]" captionStart="FIGURES 97–107" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[296,1292,181,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-19@14.[290,1297,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 97–107. Megaselia hojerensis n. sp., 97, frons; 98, postpedicels, palps and prpboscis; 99, side of thorax; 100, left side of thorax and abdomen; 101, left view of hypopygium; 102, left hypandrium; 103, right view of hypopygium; 104, front tarsus; 105, segments 3–5 of front tarsus; 106, hind femur; 107, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925239/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="319">Figs 104 and 105</figureCitation>
). Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.8 times its length. Hairs below basal half of hind femur longer than those of anteroventral row of outer half (
<figureCitation box="[1047,1148,1879,1906]" captionStart="FIGURES 97–107" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[296,1292,181,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-19@14.[290,1297,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 97–107. Megaselia hojerensis n. sp., 97, frons; 98, postpedicels, palps and prpboscis; 99, side of thorax; 100, left side of thorax and abdomen; 101, left view of hypopygium; 102, left hypandrium; 103, right view of hypopygium; 104, front tarsus; 105, segments 3–5 of front tarsus; 106, hind femur; 107, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925239/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="319">Fig. 106</figureCitation>
). Hind tibia with about a dozen differentiated posterodorsal hairs, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wings (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 97–107" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[296,1292,181,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-19@14.[290,1297,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 97–107. Megaselia hojerensis n. sp., 97, frons; 98, postpedicels, palps and prpboscis; 99, side of thorax; 100, left side of thorax and abdomen; 101, left view of hypopygium; 102, left hypandrium; 103, right view of hypopygium; 104, front tarsus; 105, segments 3–5 of front tarsus; 106, hind femur; 107, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925239/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="319">Fig. 107</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[211,312,1951,1978]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" pageId="13" pageNumber="319" unit="mm" value="1.85">1.85 mm</quantity>
long. Costal index 0.47. Costal ratios 3.5: 1.8: 1. Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity box="[1190,1291,1951,1978]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="13" pageNumber="319" unit="mm" value="0.12">0.12 mm</quantity>
long. Vein 3 hair 
<quantity box="[202,302,1987,2014]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="319" unit="mm" value="0.02">0.02 mm</quantity>
long. 4 axillary bristles, the outermost being 
<quantity box="[810,910,1987,2014]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="13" pageNumber="319" unit="mm" value="0.12">0.12 mm</quantity>
long. Sc not reaching R1. Haltere knob pale.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
